 The set of transformations $(\pi ,c)\in {\rm MAut}({RS}^{3e}_{2,2^m})$ such that  $\pi (1,0)=(1,0)$, $\pi (0,0)=\left(d,1\right)$, and $(b,1)=(0,0)$  coincides with the set of transformations of  Type 2 in the statement of Theorem   \ref{thm18}. 
